ity-making to continue, infrastructure redistributes risk elsewhere, a process that results from and that creates imaginaries of what non-city landscapes should be. Using ethnographic and historical accounts, Saguin demonstrates how people—powerful and marginalized—interact with the state and the environment to produce a thriving but unequal urban landscape.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aHuman ecologyzPhilippines. 0aPolitical ecologyzPhilippineszManilay20th century. 0aPolitical ecologyzPhilippineszManilay21st century. 7aNATURE / Ecology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2022 Englishz978311099319608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2022z9783110993134oZDB-23-DPM08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z97831107664930 cprintz978052038266440uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520382671?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520382671423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520382671/original  a978-3-11-076649-3  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099319-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-DPMb2022